71-8228.Regional medical director, defined.

Regional medical director means a physician licensed under the Uniform Credentialing Act.

SourceLaws 1997, LB 626, § 28;Laws 1999, LB 594, § 62;Laws 2007, LB296, § 689;Laws 2007, LB463, § 1303;Laws 2023, LB227, § 102.
